# Core non-negotiables (v1)

## Architecture & data
- Neo4j is the primary memory (graph-first).
- Everything is multi-tenant. Every write/query must be scoped by `orgId` (and `userId` where relevant). No cross-org visibility.
- Embeddings are mandatory for semantic retrieval and must be linked back to the originating file/artifact.

## AI & observability
- Every AI call MUST be logged with: model, input tokens, output tokens, total tokens, cost estimate, timestamp, orgId, and fileId (if applicable).
- AI calls must be configurable via environment variables (model selection, keys).

## Development & infra
- Local environment must run via `docker compose up` (no hidden cloud dependency for dev).
- Local object storage uses MinIO (S3-compatible). Production/staging uses Cloudflare R2 via the same S3 client configuration.

## Scope calls
- MongoDB is not used in v1. Do not add Mongo-based persistence.

